The paper deals with supervised representation learning for semantic analysis tasks such as ranking and information retrieval. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel model for representation learning, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper makes use of web-scale collaborative skills data, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
